      "frameId": "f-0",
      "visualKind": "shape",
      "title": "<h1>Main Problem with Registration</h1><p>Users are struggling to register successfully in our app, particularly on mobile devices. Drop-offs are especially high on step 2 of onboarding — “Create Account.” This creates friction before users can even explore workouts or meal plans.</p><p><strong>Registration Flow – Current Issues &amp; Insights</strong></p><p><strong>Core Problem:</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\">Current flow requires users to:<ol><li data-list=\"ordered\">Enter email</li><li data-list=\"ordered\">Create a password</li><li data-list=\"ordered\">Confirm email via code</li><li data-list=\"ordered\">Choose fitness goals</li><li data-list=\"ordered\">Set preferences</li><li data-list=\"ordered\">→ This is too long for mobile-first onboarding.</li></ol></li></ol><p></p><p><strong>User Feedback Highlights:</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\">“I just wanted to browse first, not set 10 preferences.”</li><li data-list=\"bullet\">“I didn’t get the confirmation email.”</li><li data-list=\"bullet\">“I thought I signed up with Apple, but it asked me for a password again.”</li></ol><p></p><p><strong>Key Observations:</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\">38% drop-off during email confirmation step</li><li data-list=\"bullet\">1 in 5 users abandon when asked for too much upfront</li><li data-list=\"bullet\">Many users try to sign in with Google/Apple but don’t complete the flow</li></ol>"
    },
    {
      "id": "n-1",
